<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 31 at 12:16AM MDT until July 31 at 12:45AM MDT by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1245 AM MDT
FOR NORTHEASTERN GARFIELD...WESTERN ROOSEVELT...SOUTHEASTERN VALLEY
AND NORTHWESTERN MCCONE COUNTIES...
At 1216 AM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 8 miles east of Lustre to 10 miles south of Frazer to
near Rock Creek Rec Area, moving southeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Wolf Point, Fort Peck, The Pines Rec Area, Lustre, Bredette, Frazer,
Nelson Creek Rec Area, Rock Creek Rec Area, Fort Peck Marina, Duck
Creek Rec Area, Oswego, Volt and Haxby.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
